</LG>
<LG>
<L>Things without life &s;hall in this Chorus join,</L>
<L>And, dumb to others' prai&s;e, be loud in mine.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>The <HI>Snow-drop,</HI> who, in habit white and plain,</L>
<L>Comes on, the <HI>Herald</HI> of fair FLORA'S train;</L>
<L>The Coxcomb <HI>Crocus,</HI> flow'r of &s;imple note,</L>
<L>Who by her &s;ide &s;truts in a <HI>Herald</HI>'s coat;</L>
<L><PB N="109" REF="105">
The <HI>Tulip,</HI> idly glaring to the view,</L>
<L>Who, tho' no Clown, his birth from Holland drew,</L>
<L>Who, once full dre&s;s'd, fears from his place to &s;tir,</L>
<L>The fop of flow'rs, the MORE of a Parterre;</L>
<L>The <HI>Wood-bine,</HI> who her <HI>Elm</HI> in marriage meets,</L>
